ABUJA (SundiataPost) – With the addition of 403 new cases on Sunday night, the number of COVID-19 cases in Nigeria has hit 16,085.Another twist to the increasing spread of the pandemic in Nigeria is that Gombe State recorded more new cases than Lagos. Out of the 403 new cases reported by the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) on Saturday night, 73 new infections happened in Gombe while Lagos State came second with 68 new cases. Kano and Edo came came third and fourth with 46 and 36 new cases respectively. The full report is as follows: 403 new cases of #COVID19 Gombe-73Lagos-68Kano-46Edo-36FCT-35Nasarawa-31Kaduna-17Oyo-16Abia-15Delta-13Borno-13Plateau-8Niger-7Rivers-7Enugu-6Ogun-6Kebbi-3Ondo-1Anambra-1Imo-1 16,085 confirmed5,220 discharged420 deaths See state by state breakdown below: ABUJA - The Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC) has reported 64 new cases COVID-19 in the country. In an update on the spread of the pandemic released late on Monday night, the NCDC said 34 new cases emanated from Lagos while 15 new infections were reported in the Federal… April 27, 2020 In "Top Stories" ABUJA - With the latest report of the Nigeria Centre for Disease Control (NCDC), Nigeria has gone above one thousand COVID-19 cases. The latest figure is 1,095 confirmed cases, the figure having swollen up by additional 114 new cases as at late on Friday. one surprising aspect of the latest… April 25, 2020 In "Top Stories" The Kano State government has confirmed the death of two more patients who tested positive for coronavirus (COVID-19) in the state. The state Ministry of Health announced this in a tweet, saying that was the situation in Kano as of 12:15pm on Monday. This brings the total number of COVID-19… April 27, 2020 In "Top Stories"